‚ÄúTamen La‚Äù, A 77 years old lady met during the visit of the village at the feet of the ganden monastery. She witnessed the Chinese action among 1950 and 1959 when the monastery was completely destroyed. The monastery was then rebuilt by Chinese themselves but the scar inside Tibetan people never found relief. When she questioned about her life she told us that she never been outside her village except for one time when she visited Lhasa.
